OL,3,C'My daughter was a crime scene': Holly
OL,4,CNewton's mother recalls daughter's
OL,5,Cmurder
OL,7,F"Once at hospital, I was unable to
OL,8,Feven touch my daughter, hug her, kiss
OL,9,Fher or hold her hand.
OL,11,F"My daughter was a crime scene, she
OL,12,Fwas evidence."
OL,14,FMs Trussler said Holly and MacPhail
OL,15,Fhad a typical teenage relationship at
OL,16,Fthe beginning. Holly was caring and
OL,17,Ftried to help her first and only
OL,18,Fboyfriend - who had autism and
OL,19,Flearning difficulties - learn to read
OL,20,Fby getting books from the library.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/9
