OL,3,C'My daughter was a crime scene': Holly
OL,4,CNewton's mother recalls daughter's
OL,5,Cmurder
OL,7,FAs she addressed the court, MacPhail
OL,8,Fjoined via video link, and she told
OL,9,Fthem that "Holly is missed beyond
OL,10,Fwords and can never be described and
OL,11,Fnever be forgotten."
OL,13,FJudge Mr Justice Hilliard thanked her
OL,14,Ffor her words, adding: "You have done
OL,15,FHolly's memory proud by the way you
OL,16,Fhave handled it."
OL,18,FOn the first day of a two-day
OL,19,Fsentencing, there was discussion about
OL,20,FMacPhail's learning difficulties, his
OL,21,Fautism and culpability.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/9
